wdi-EG.ELC.COAL.ZS.def: Sources of electricity refer to the inputs used to generate electricity. Coal refers to all coal and brown coal, both primary (including hard coal and lignite-brown coal) and derived fuels (including patent fuel, coke oven coke, gas coke, coke oven gas, and blast furnace gas). Peat is also included in this category.
wdi-EG.ELC.COAL.ZS.name: Electricity production from coal sources
